aVMy knees still buckle every time I get on a stage.
p426
aVMy self-confidence can be measured out
p427
aVin teaspoons mixed into my poetry,
p428
aVand it still always tastes funny in my mouth.
p429
aVBut in Hiroshima, some people were wiped clean away,
p430
aVleaving only a wristwatch or a diary page.
p431
aVSo no matter that I have inhibitions to fill all my pockets,
p432
aVI keep trying,
p433
aVhoping that one day I'll write a poem
